 in the field; demonstrate how yoga can mitigate stress and tension, particularly amid an increased focus on standardized curricula and testing; and offer lessons learned and practical insights into planning, implementing, and running these programs. Rich in detail and accessible to nonspecialists, Stories of School Yoga presents helpful resources and a nuanced, on-the-ground look at the yoga-in-schools movement.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aAffective education. 0aHatha yoga for childrenxStudy and teaching. 0aHatha yoga for teenagersxStudy and teaching. 0aSchool childrenxMental health. 4aEducation : Education. 4aEducation : Teacher Education. 4aEducation : Urban Education. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Yoga. 4aSociology : Sociology. 7aEDUCATION / Curricula.2bisacsh1 aBrook, Michelle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCollings, Peggy C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFlynn, Lisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHyde, Andrea M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHyde, Andrea M., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJohnson, Janet D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnson, Janet D., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKrodman-Collins, Debra A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarie, Dee, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcGlauflin, Helene, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeeker, Lindsay, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOliveira, Peg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPhilibert, Carla Tantillo, e